records.addlTxt: Per modification on 6/24/2016

Defendant Thomas M Warriner-Jaeger in court with attorney Esther Cohen Lee.  Defendant Thomas M Warriner-Jaeger in custody.  Zachary A Wittchow appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Matter is set here for sentence modification.  The court has reviewed all materials submitted and will GRANT the sentence modification based on the Wuensch and Robinson cases.  The court makes the distinction that this modification is not a result of reflection but a change in the the court's analysis for reasons placed on the record.
There are no direct victims and there is no restitution.  Sentencing arguments by counsels.   The court sentences the defendant to serve 6 months in the House of Correction, consecutive to initial confinement being served in Fond du Lac County case 10CF320.  
The court orders defendant to pay all mandatory costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, DNA surcharge, provide DNA sample and pay costs by  6-25-2021 and failure to do so will result in entry of civil judgment
-The Court ordered collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b).
 Court advised the defendant that as a convicted felon he may no longer use or possess any firearms; also he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been restored.
The court directs counsel to inform the defendant of his appeal rights and to file the appropriate form. within 20 days.
At the request of Atty Lee the court is directing that the Clerk of Courts office fax a copy of the Judgment of Conviction in this case to the Registrar Office at Stanley Correctional Institution.
Defendant remanded.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Thomas M Warriner-Jaeger in court with attorney Darryl E. Smith.  Defendant Thomas M Warriner-Jaeger in custody.  Nicholas Steven Cerwin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  AA.

Defendant  advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.   Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant is advised he is a convicted felon and may not possess any firearms; also defendant is advised he is unable to vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.

Sentencing Proceeded. Statements by the State, defense counsel and defendant. 

The Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 3 1/2 YEARS.  INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 18 MONTHS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 2 YEARS, consecutive to any other sentence, credit for 93 days.
Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
-Restitution set at zero
-Court costs and victim/witness surcharges are to be collected by DOC from up to 25% of prison funds, balance to be paid by 10/17/2018; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment.
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge  to be collected by DOC from up to 25% of prison funds, balance to be paid by 10/17/2018; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment.
CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
-AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
-Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzers
-No alcohol or controlled substances
-Employment or school
-Successfully complete a Cognitive Thinking Behavioral Modification Program

Court advised the defendant that as a convicted felon he may no longer use or possess any firearms; also he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been restored.
